[Maps of Nepal can be seen at http://tinyurl.com/ydf8ojtj and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5239887,139.
Nawalparasi district in south-central Nepal is one of the 75 districts of Nepal; Chitwan district neighbors it on the east, and the Indian border on the south (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nawalparasi_District). - Mod.ML]

******
[2] Dhankuta
Date: Mon 7 Aug 2017
Source: Kathmandu Post [edited]
http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2017-08-07/scrub-typhus-claims-1-infects-3-in-dhankuta.html


A child died and 3 others were taken ill due to scrub typhus in Khalsa Chintang Sahidbhumi Rural Municipality and Parkhibas Municipality in Dhankuta district [Province One].

The identity of the deceased is yet to be established. She [died] during the course of treatment at the Dharan-based BP Koirala Institute of Health Sciences.

According to Dr Madan Kumar Upadhyay, senior medical superintendent of the District Hospital, Dhankuta, 3 children have been tested positive.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Dhankuta, with a population of 26 440 residents, is a hill town located in Dhankuta district of eastern Nepal (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhankuta).

There have been prior reports on scrub typhus cases in Nepal earlier this year (2017) and last year (see also's below). - Mod.ML]
